Package org.svvrl.goal.core.comp.rank

Class RankState

java.lang.Object
org.svvrl.goal.core.comp.rank.RankState
public class RankState
extends java.lang.Object
This class provide an implementation of states in the complements constructed by the rank-based construction. Such states are called rank states here. A rank state can be a set of states S, a tuple (S, O, f), or a tuple (S, O, f, i) where S is a set of reachable states, O is a set of reachable states that owe a visit to odd ranks, f is a level ranking, and i is an even rank to be checked. We call a rank state ranked if it contains a level ranking. In a ranked rank state, the set S is not stored separately because it is the same as the domain of the level ranking. By the rank-based construction, a rank state is valid if several conditions are satisfied but these conditions are not checked in this class. For example, O should be a subset of S but this is not checked in this class.
Author:
"Ming-Hsien Tsai"
